<p>
  <span class="nym">Lothar</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Old High German</span> <i>hlūt, lūt</i>, <span class="lang">Old Saxon</span> <i>hlūd</i> from <span class="lang">Proto-Germanic</span> <i>*hlūdaz, *hlūþaz</i> 'loud; famous, renowned' + <span class="lang">Old High German</span> <i>heri</i> 'host, army'..
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of a 6th C king of the Franks, two 7th C kings of the Franks, an 8th C king of the Franks, a 9th C Holy Roman Emperor and king of Italy, a 9th C king of Lotharingia, a 10th C king of Italy, a 10th C king of the Franks, and a 12th C Holy Roman Emperor.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>The name was sometimes conflated with <a class="nym" href="Luther">Luther</a>.</p>
  
  


